Barclays, Lloyds Purchase Stake in U.K. Hotel Chain, Times Says

-- B y   R e n e e   L a w r e n c e
-- 
2011-03-05T12:47:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/barclays-lloyds-purchase-stake-in-u-k-hotel-chain-times-says.html
  Barclays Plc (BARC)  and  Lloyds Banking
Group Plc (LLOY)  have bought a 45.4 percent stake in  Kew Green Hotels 
as part of a 39 million-pound ($63.4 million) debt for equity
swap, the Times reported, without citing anyone.  Kew Green, which runs 22 hotels under franchises including
Holiday Inn, Courtyard by Marriott and Days Hotel, has cut its
debt burden from 120 million pounds to 80 million pounds and
secured a 3 million-pound refurbishment facility, the Times
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Renee Lawrence in London at 
